Misc.name: Welcome

Misc.description:
You have one chance to solve each board. More information is provided in the challenge.

Some more information regarding the challenge:
- Initially, Bob sets up the coins in the chessboard completely randomly.
- After, that, he shows Alice which is the answer coin.
- Then, Alice flips a coin strategically so as to communicate to you which coin is the correct one.
- After all of these tasks are done, you see the board and you have to figure out in one go which is the correct coin. You do not know the initial configuration of the board, neither the coin which Alice flipped.
- You have to answer the coin index (starting from 0) below which the paper is there.
Misc.name: Coin Flip

Misc.description:
Can you help my friend, test *gPOW*?
gPOW stands for Graphical Proof of Work!
Misc.name: gPOW

My friend challenged me at a game. But, I suck at it.
I have been at it for hours but I always end up losing :')
Can you help me beat him?

Discord bots are awesome! Some can answer any question you ask, while some ask you questions.

* Use channel #botspam. Tag the bot @Riddler and he will dm you ;) * Be fast with your answers, the bot doesn't entertain those who are slow :V
Misc.name: Riddle me this

Misc.description:
My friend went to Mars on a secret mission.
Its been 2 years since I last heard from him. So, I decided to go to the NASA headquarters.
They told me that it is uncertain whether my friend is dead or alive. They have set up a Secure Communication line to Mars. But, the person on the other side could either be my friend or an alien.

Can you help me identify whether he is my friend or an alien?
Misc.name: SCP

OSINT.description: Some hacK3r-man stole data from Saptang Labs. He hid it somewhere on the internet. Now, being an OSINT expert it's your job to retrieve what was stolen.

OSINT.description:
Whenever I look at this picture, three questions come to my mind.
1) What are those protuding like structures?
2) What is this place?
3) How old are they?
Can you help me figure this out?
Flag: jadeCTF{name_place_age}
Replace spaces, if any, in name, place and age with underscore.

OSINT.description:
"Picture of a tree?" Weird!

**Note:** Once you logically connect everything, you will know what the answer is. Enclose the answer in jadeCTF{} to get your flag.

Pwn.description:
In his DBMS course, Shekhar was learning about CRUD operations. He was taught these operations in SQL, but he wanted to try them out in C. He wrote a program for reading data from input, and then scrambling it so other users can't figure out what is stored.
He gave me the binary to test it, could you help me out?

Pwn.description:
Sourav wanted to calculate his compatibility with this girl he has a huge crush on. He thought of writing an application for this. But his code didn't work. It didn't show any compatibility/love percentage whatsoever.
His application is provided. Help him understand why his code doesn't work.

He couldn't wait for the new episodes, and downloaded an application which would "apparently" get him all the episodes straight away.
Sadly, it turned out to be a malware, and encrypted all the files in his system.
He needs your help. Provided is the malware and one of his files. **WARNING! THIS CHALLENGE CONTAINS A LIVE MALWARE**
